metadata.name: Word-eating worms #54
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.

An old letter recounts the problems and feelings caused by woodworms: worms known to eat not only the beams and wood of houses, but also old books. As an analogy to this daily occurrence, emoticons appear and with the good spirit of simplifying they begin to gnaw away so much literary flourish.

The piece puts in counterpoint two forms of communication: emoticons and traditional writing. Here an inevitable contrast is sought between the standardization of the feelings of emojis, and the excessive flourishes of texts, possibly already from other times.

Original flute (tap & frullato), cello (pizz) and marimba samplers.
((click to start sound))

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

metadata.name: Bifurcations (straight lines) #17
metadata.description:
An line drawn on the screen until it bifurcates. The same is done for each new line, and so on. The color changes over the time, under the rules of five available color modes: random, complementary, grayscale, monochrome and boogie-woogie (red, yellow, blue, black and white, like in the Mondrian boogie-woogie paintings)

Press P to download a high resolution image, and Space to pause the animation.

metadata.name: pure  #20
metadata.description:
A polygon is generated by a random number of vertices. Each polygon consists of triangles which are connected to each other. The vertices receive pure color values from Red Green Blue, which also can create Magenta Yellow Cyan as well Black and White. Each vertex also gets an opacity value.
The colors are blended between the neighboring vertices and create a unique colored polygon.
The vertices occupy specific positions in space which are reflected in the background and become observable during the rotation of the construct.
Canvas and background receive colors per token as well to create different oppositions to the object.
The polygon rotates slowly to experience a mixture of a two and three dimensional experience.
Additionally the perspective can be adjusted for a quicker rotation around the object.

metadata.name: Mustachioed #150
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.
Mustachioed is a historical research that aims to link the history of the mustache to the digital world.
Each piece of mustachioed is a ticket to enter this unique world where different samples of mustaches are collected.
Who has the chance to register an outstanding mustache to their names?

metadata.name: Sketchbook Splash #486
metadata.description:
A splash of color on some scribbled shapes.

There are several keybindings to modify the image:
'1' - Toggles watercolors
'2' - Toggles overlaying constrast shapes 
'3' - Toggles sketch outlines
'4' - Toggles shape/splatter clipping (will fill the entire canvas with watercolor!)
'B' - Cycles borders; black, white, all colors in the palette being used, and no border

Play around to find something you like, and then press 'S' to download a copy of your image. 
You can also modify the URL parameters at the end of the URL to change the size of the image, such as &x=2560&y=1440. Keep in mind that this will result in a slightly different image, but colors/shapes/general layout will remain the same. The default size is 2048x2048.

metadata.name: Alleles #200
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Detailed investigation of the presented genetic information suggests subject may posess a predeliction for intermittent episodes of delusions of grandeur and lack of self-confidence, yet also posesses an aptitude for unparalled creative problem solving abilities and determination. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 200-207cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 78-82 years.

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #190
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - jump
[ tap ] - increase velocity briefly

Created with Three.js + rapier.js
